rows.label: qst103908_msg0001
rows.name:
Huh? Wha-wha-what? How did
friends get back, mo?

rows.label: qst103908_msg0002
rows.name:
There are strong monsters there, so
Kebubu thought friends would either
give up or become Superbian soil...mo...

rows.label: qst103908_msg0003
rows.name:
Waaah! Don't be angry, mo!
Kebubu will tell the truth, mo!

rows.label: qst103908_msg0005
rows.name:
The handling fee is a teeeeeny
bit more than friends expect,
so it was hard to say...mo...

rows.label: qst103908_msg0007
rows.name:
Being a courier in
Superbia is tough, mo!

rows.label: qst103908_msg0008
rows.name:
Have to slip shiny things
under soldiers' armor, or
give them "gifts"...mo...

rows.label: qst103908_msg0009
rows.name:
To soothe such stress, Kebubu
sometimes goes to a hot spring...mo...
but only very rarely, mo!

rows.label: qst103908_msg0010
rows.name:
A shipment of 82,166G comes
in... and 66,554G gets sent
to Liberalitas, mo.

rows.label: qst103908_msg0011
rows.name:
That's the honest truth, mo!
Kebubu takes nothing more, mo.

rows.label: qst103908_msg0012
rows.name:
Kebubu doesn't know the shipping
cost from the port in Liberalitas
to Iyasaki Village, mo.

rows.label: qst103908_msg0013
rows.name:
If friends go to Rigitte Harbor
in Liberalitas, there's an old
courier man named Schuchit.

rows.label: qst103908_msg0014
rows.name: Friends should ask him directly, mo.

rows.label: qst103908_msg0101
rows.name:
Just because Nopon are small,
they tell us to dock our big
ships at the tiny pier...mo...

rows.label: qst103908_msg0102
rows.name:
But they don't say that to
ships from the Avaritia Trade
Guild... It's so unfair, mo!
